          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The object that the receiver (or its parent) makes available to other applications or threads, or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "nil",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " if there is no root object.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To get a proxy to this object in another application or thread, invoke the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsconnection/1478061-rootproxyforconnectionwithregist",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " class method with the appropriate arguments.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Changing the root object only affects new connection requests and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsconnection/1478065-rootproxy",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " messages to established ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSConnection",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " objects—applications that have proxies to the old root object can still send messages through it.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
